### ===========================================
### MOBILE API TESTS - Laravel Sanctum
### ===========================================
###
### These endpoints are designed for mobile apps (iOS, Android, React Native, Flutter)
### Uses token-based authentication (no cookies, no CSRF)
###
### FEATURES:
### ✅ Stateless authentication
### ✅ Token-based (Sanctum)
### ✅ No CSRF tokens required
### ✅ JSON responses
### ✅ 2FA support
###
### ===========================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiPrefix = /api

# Variables to store tokens (update after login)
@token =1|2IXbUbpTeVCVTLn27yv0aDAJbkEOjjPR696z9CDY83ed298c 
@userId = 


### ===========================================
### 1. REGISTER (Mobile)
### ===========================================

### Test 1.1: Successful Registration
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Mobile User",
  "email": "mobile@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "password_confirmation": "Password123!"
}

### Expected Response:
### 201 Created
### {
###   "message": "User registered successfully",
###   "user": { ... },
###   "token": "1|XXXXX..."  <- Copy this token!
### }

###

### Test 1.2: Registration - Validation Errors
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "123"
}

###

### Test 1.3: Registration - Duplicate Email
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Duplicate User",
  "email": "mobile@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "password_confirmation": "Password123!"
}

###


### ===========================================
### 2. LOGIN (Mobile)
### ===========================================

### Test 2.1: Successful Login (No 2FA)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "mobile@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Expected Response:
### 200 OK
### {
###   "message": "Login successful",
###   "user": { ... },
###   "token": "2|XXXXX..."  <- Copy this token!
### }

###

### Test 2.2: Login - Invalid Credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "mobile@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}

###

### Test 2.3: Login - User with 2FA Enabled
### (First enable 2FA for a user, then test)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "user-with-2fa@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Expected Response:
### 200 OK
### {
###   "message": "Two-factor authentication required",
###   "requires_2fa": true,
###   "user_id": 123
### }

###


### ===========================================
### 3. TWO-FACTOR AUTHENTICATION
### ===========================================

### Test 3.1: Verify 2FA Code
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/verify-2fa HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "user_id": 123,
  "code": "123456"
}

### Replace "123456" with actual code from Google Authenticator

###

### Test 3.2: Verify 2FA - Invalid Code
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/verify-2fa HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "user_id": 123,
  "code": "000000"
}

###


### ===========================================
### 4. AUTHENTICATED REQUESTS
### ===========================================
### IMPORTANT: Copy token from login/register response
### and paste it in the @token variable at the top!

### Test 4.1: Get Current User Profile
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/me HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Test 4.2: Get User (Alternative Endpoint)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/user HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Test 4.3: Authenticated Request - Invalid Token
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/me HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### Expected: 401 Unauthorized

###

### Test 4.4: Authenticated Request - No Token
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/me HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### Expected: 401 Unauthorized

###


### ===========================================
### 5. LOGOUT
### ===========================================

### Test 5.1: Logout (Revoke Current Token)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/logout HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response:
### 200 OK
### {
###   "message": "Logged out successfully"
### }

###

### Test 5.2: Logout - No Token
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/logout HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### Expected: 401 Unauthorized

###


### ===========================================
### TESTING WORKFLOW FOR MOBILE API
### ===========================================
###
### 1. REGISTER NEW USER
###    - Run Test 1.1
###    - Copy the token from response
###    - Paste it in @token variable at top of file
###
### 2. TEST AUTHENTICATED ENDPOINTS
###    - Run Test 4.1 (Get current user)
###    - Should return user data
###
### 3. LOGOUT
###    - Run Test 5.1
###    - Token is now invalid
###
### 4. LOGIN AGAIN
###    - Run Test 2.1
###    - Get new token
###    - Update @token variable
###
### 5. TEST OTHER FEATURES
###    - Use the token in Authorization header
###    - All protected endpoints require: Authorization: Bearer {token}
###
### ===========================================


### ===========================================
### INTEGRATION WITH MOBILE APP
### ===========================================
###
### Example for React Native / Flutter / Swift / Kotlin:
###
### 1. REGISTRATION
###    POST http://yourapi.com/api/register
###    Body: { name, email, password, password_confirmation }
###    Response: { token, user }
###    -> Save token in secure storage (AsyncStorage, SecureStore, Keychain)
###
### 2. LOGIN
###    POST http://yourapi.com/api/login
###    Body: { email, password }
###    Response: { token, user } OR { requires_2fa: true, user_id }
###    -> If requires_2fa, show 2FA input screen
###    -> Save token in secure storage
###
### 3. 2FA VERIFICATION
###    POST http://yourapi.com/api/verify-2fa
###    Body: { user_id, code }
###    Response: { token, user }
###    -> Save token in secure storage
###
### 4. AUTHENTICATED REQUESTS
###    GET/POST http://yourapi.com/api/*
###    Headers: { Authorization: "Bearer {token}" }
###    
### 5. LOGOUT
###    POST http://yourapi.com/api/logout
###    Headers: { Authorization: "Bearer {token}" }
###    -> Remove token from storage
###
### ===========================================


### ===========================================
### RESPONSE FORMATS
### ===========================================
###
### SUCCESS (200/201):
### {
###   "message": "Success message",
###   "user": { id, name, email, balance, ... },
###   "token": "1|xxxxx..."
### }
###
### VALIDATION ERROR (422):
### {
###   "message": "The given data was invalid.",
###   "errors": {
###     "email": ["The email field is required."],
###     "password": ["The password must be at least 8 characters."]
###   }
### }
###
### AUTHENTICATION ERROR (401):
### {
###   "message": "Unauthenticated."
### }
###
### SERVER ERROR (500):
### {
###   "message": "Server Error",
###   "exception": "..."
### }
###
### ===========================================


### ===========================================
### NOTES FOR MOBILE DEVELOPERS
### ===========================================
###
### ✅ NO CSRF tokens needed (stateless API)
### ✅ NO cookies needed (token-based)
### ✅ Token format: "Bearer {token}"
### ✅ Token should be stored securely on device
### ✅ Include token in Authorization header for all protected routes
### ✅ Handle 401 responses -> redirect to login
### ✅ Handle 422 responses -> show validation errors
### ✅ Tokens don't expire by default (configure in sanctum.php if needed)
### ✅ User can have multiple tokens (multiple devices)
### ✅ Logout only revokes current token (other devices stay logged in)
###
### ===========================================
